  "active_lock_reason": "resolved",
  "body": "Solidity errors and warnings are currently printed in full red or yellow color. While some color is nice, printing the entire text in a single color isn't comfortable to read.\r\n\r\nI'd say only the error category (`Warning`, `ParserError`, ...) should be printed in the corresponding yellow or red color.\r\n\r\nIt could also be nice to experiment with further formatting of other things like the source code location, the error description itself, or the `^----^` marker that points at the error location, using bold, dimming, or more colors.\r\n\r\n",
